#Text=Dothan
#Text=Dothan
#Text=is a city in southeastern
#Text=Alabama
#Text=, serving as the county seat of Houston
#Text=County , and the chief city of the western Wiregrass region , an area encompassing portions of southeastern Alabama , southwestern Georgia , and the panhandle of Florida .
#Text=Its population in 2018 was about 68,000 , making it the largest metropolitan area in southeastern Alabama .
#Text=History
#Text=Dothan began as " Poplar Head " , a stop along the main trail that ran through this portion of the state during the early 19th century .
#Text=It was incorporated in 1885 , and renamed after the village mentioned in Genesis 37:17 , which reads " let us go to Dothan " .
#Text=The city quickly became a hub for local agriculture and industry , especially the peanut business , and its annual National Peanut Festival ( since 1938 ) reflects this heritage .
#Text=Dothan has long proclaimed itself the " Peanut Capital of the World " , as approximately one-quarter of the peanuts grown in the U.S. are grown within 75 miles of the city .

column1: #Text=Movie Gallery , a national movie rental chain , has its national headquarters here .
#Text=Climate
#Text=Dothan has a humid subtropical climate , with hot , sticky summers and generally mild winters .
#Text=Snowfall is rare , and when it does come , it seldom accumulates to any great degree or remains for very long .
#Text=Summer temperatures easily reach or more , while the average winter temperature is .
#Text=By plane
#Text=Dothan has one commercial airport , northwest of the city in the tiny village of Napier Field .
#Text=It is served by ExpressJet , a subsidiary of Delta Air Lines , flying to and from Atlanta International Airport .
#Text=Dothan Regional Airport offers a full range of airport services and amenities ; for further information , visit their website at Dothan Regional Airport .
#Text=By train
#Text=There is no passenger rail service to Dothan .
#Text=The nearest Amtrak station is in Birmingham .
#Text=Chipley , Florida had an Amtrak station prior to the landfall of Hurricane Katrina , but damage to the tracks in northwestern Florida forced its closure .
#Text=Amtrak has proposed restoring the line , but there is no plan to do so as of March 2019 .
#Text=By bus
#Text=Dothan is served by Greyhound Bus Lines .
#Text=The station is at 285 S. Foster St. , +1 334-792-1191 .
#Text=Further information and hours of operation may be found at Dothan Greyhound Station .
#Text=By car
#Text=U.S. Highways 231 , 431 and 84 all intersect in Dothan , as do several state highways .
#Text=There is no interstate service in this part of Alabama , but the three highways named above are all four-laned for several miles beyond the Dothan city limits .
#Text=U.S. 231 is four-laned all the way north to Montgomery , and all the way south to Panama City .
#Text=The city is encircled by a four-lane bypass , known as the " Ross-Clark Circle .

#Text=Traffic on the Ross-Clark Circle can be quite heavy , especially during  rush hour " and around lunchtime .

column1: #Text=See
#Text=US Army Aviation Museum
#Text=.
#Text=Located on Ft. Rucker , which lies just north of the town of Daleville about 20 miles north and west of Dothan .

#Text=Many people do not realize that military aviation existed long before the creation of the Air Force in 1949 ; all military aircraft used in World War II , for instance , were either Army , Navy or Marine Corps aircraft , with the majority being Army airplanes .
#Text=This museum pays tribute to the history of Army aviation , with sizable displays of Army aircraft -- fixed-wing and rotary -- from the earliest twentieth century to today .
#Text=A variety of life-sized dioramas , films and interpretive material are available .
#Text=Admission is free .
#Text=Ft.
#Text=Rucker is a " closed post " ; guards at the post gates will require identification to enter , even for museum visitors .
#Text=Dr. George Washington Carver Monument
#Text=( at the National Peanut Festival Fairgrounds ) .
#Text=This monument honors the African-American genius whose creative work resulted in hundreds of new products created from peanuts , sweet potatoes and other plants native to the South .
#Text=Most of these were derived from peanuts , which are the principal agricultural product of the Wiregrass region -- of which Dothan is the principal city .
#Text=Dothan Area Botanical Gardens
#Text=.
#Text=Enjoy the old Southern-style of gardening , and see what works in the Wiregrass .
#Text=A tranquil , paved nature trail meanders through a beautiful rose garden , through herbs , daylilies , camellias , azaleas , past a peaceful pond , Victorian gazebo and a demonstration garden .
#Text=Dothan Opera House
#Text=.
#Text=Built in 1915 , represents the elegance of turn-of-the-century southern life .
#Text=Theatre performances , spectacular concerts , symphonies , ballet performances , and many other cultural events are regularly held in this landmark .
#Text=Tours are available upon request .
#Text=Joseph statue
#Text=( in Millennium Park ) .
#Text=The status is a ten-feet tall cast bronze sculpture , located in the historic downtown area .
#Text=It depicts the Bible verse , " For I heard them say , Let us go to Dothan " ( Genesis 37:17 ) , which inspired city founders in 1885 to change the name of the town from Poplar Head to Dothan .
#Text=Landmark Park Agricultural Museum and Starlab Planetarium
#Text=.
#Text=The official agriculture museum of the State of Alabama .
#Text=Visit a 1900s farmstead , complete with farmhouse , outhouses , and farm animals .
#Text=Stroll the boardwalk and nature trail , see a planetarium show , have a picnic , tour Phase I of the Alabama Agricultural Museum , or catch one of the park 's many special events .
#Text=In the Planetarium , night skies are shown as they appear in season .
#Text=Constellations are displayed as they relate to mythology .
#Text=The park also has a new playground .
#Text=A pavilion near the playground is available for park visitors and children 's parties .
#Text=Houston-Love Memorial Library
#Text=, 212 W. Burdeshaw Street ( downtown Dothan across from the main post office ) .
#Text=Maria 's Vineyard
#Text=.
#Text=Nestled in a grove of oak and pecan trees , the Vineyard offers a casual place to host an event either outside or inside in the Vineyard House .
#Text=Peanut Monument
#Text=.
#Text=At the Visitor Information Center helps to proclaim Dothan as the " Peanut Capital of the World " .
#Text=Peanuts Around Town
#Text=.
#Text=A public art project organized by The Downtown Group consisting of 5-ft-tall peanut sculptures that are decorated in various fashions and displayed around Dothan .
#Text=Wiregrass Museum of Art
#Text=.
#Text=Includes five galleries feature changing exhibitions of visual and decorative arts in the historic building .
#Text=Also features ARTventures , a hands-on exhibit for children and a gift gallery for shopping .
#Text=World 's Smallest City Block
#Text=( at the intersection of North Appletree , Museum , and Troy streets ) .

#Text=This land triangle features a stop sign , a yield sign , a street sign , and a granite marker placed by the Camellia Garden Club on May 1 , 1964 stating that the block is the world 's smallest city block .
